China passes first anti-terrorism law

 
 By Compiled by Democrat-Gazette staff from wire reports
 


 
 
 This article was originally published December 28, 2015 at 4:59 a.m.
 
 
 Updated December 28, 2015 at 4:59 a.m.
 

Chinese paramilitary police stand guard in the popular shopping and tourist area of Wangfujing in the capital city, Beijing, on Sunday.


 Shoppers walk by as Chinese paramilitary police Sunday in Beijing’s popular shopping and nightlife area of Sanlitun.

BEIJING -- China's legislature on Sunday approved the country's first anti-terrorism law, despite criticism of its requirements that tech companies share information with the government.


